[This may not sound like much, but for a country like South Sudan, riven by war and unrest, this is a great step forward. If they are making cold chain equipment available to the rural veterinary services it implies that the "huge" purchases go beyond merely antibiotics and drugs but include vaccines; anthrax need is mentioned. If any member is aware of more detailed information, please share. Livestock disease reporting out of South Sudan is spotty, at best.

Maps of South Sudan can be seen at https://docs.unocha.org/sites/dms/SouthSudan/map_2684.pdf and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3064649,24650. Checking the maps indicates that the drug distribution may be limited to East Equatoria state, which is on the northern Kenyan border, thus explaining Kenya's possible involvement. The news report hints that the drug distribution might be limited to this Southern Sudan province. - Mod.MHJ]
